commit.message: Add high-level overview diagram of mod_authnz_external's usage to clarify that *external* authenticators run *outside* apache

Inject any AUTHORIZE_ headers set by other modules into the child process' environment array during exec_external():

- allows the external program to access authorization information set by other modules (such as mod_auth_kerb or mod_authnz_ldap)

Use apr_array for child environment variables in exec_external() instead of a fixed-size C array:

- fixes a buffer overflow in the Windows build (forgot to increment the array size)
- prevents potential future buffer overflows for users who customize the environment without incrementing the array size
- allows us to dynamically add environment entries easily at run-time

- the apr_array_push_wrapper() function wraps apr_array_push() with a simpler, more logical syntax
Cast to size_t instead of long to prevent spurious warnings about pointer truncation on 64-bit platforms (VC compiler)
Reformat mod_authnz_external.c - no code changes
Textual improvements - fixed a typo and expanded a function comment
Add nmake makefile for Windows builds + update Travis-CI config to use the nmake makefile on Windows builds
Add a note about the project license as a link to Apache.org
